automata.schelling

Class SchellingSet<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.util.AbstractCollection<E>
      • java.util.AbstractSet<T>
        • automata.schelling.SchellingSet<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - The class of the content of this set (here, SchellingCell).
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.Set<T>

    public class SchellingSet<T>
extends java.util.AbstractSet<T>
implements java.util.Set<T>
    Represents a set designed for the Schelling simulation. This set is based on Java util's Collections. It performs the following operations: - Add in O(1) ; - Remove in O(1) ; - Remove random in O(1) ;
